 king William. &sect; <HI>XXXI.</HI> The allies are defeated at Steenkirk. &sect; <HI>XXXII.</HI> Extravagatant rejoicings in France on account of this victory. &sect; <HI>XXXIII.</HI> Con&s;piracy again&s;t the life of king William, batched by the French mini&s;try. &sect; <HI>XXXIV.</HI> Mi&s;$$$riage of a de&s;ign upon Dunkirk. &sect; <HI>XXXV.</HI> The campaign is inactive on the Rhine and in Hungary. &sect; <HI>XXXVI.</HI> The duke of Savoy invades Dauphin&eacute;. &sect; <HI>XXXVII.</HI> The duke of Hanover created an elector of the empire.</P>
