<PB N="428" REF="4310">
&s;eptennial parliaments. &sect; <HI>XXXV.</HI> Duke of Argyle di&s;graced. &sect; <HI>XXXVI.</HI> Triple alliance between England, France, and Holland. &sect; <HI>XXXVII.</HI> Count $word$ the Swedi&s;h mini&s;ter in London arre&s;ted. &sect; <HI>XXXVIII.</HI> Account of the Oxford r$c$. &sect; <HI>XXXIX.</HI> The king demands an extraordinary &s;upply of the commons. &sect; <HI>XL.</HI> Divi&s;ion in the mini&s;try. &sect; <HI>XLI.</HI> The commons pa&s;s the South-&s;ea-act, the bank-act, and the general fund-act. &sect; <HI>XLII.</HI> Trial of the earl of Oxford. Act of indemnity. &sect; <HI>XLIII.</HI> Proceedings in the convocation with regard to Dr. Hoadley bi&s;hop of Bangor.</P>
