HI>XXIX.</HI> France di&s;tracted by religions di&s;putes. &sect; <HI>XXX.</HI> The mini&s;try violently oppo&s;ed in parliament. &sect; <HI>XXXI.</HI> Debate on a &s;tanding army. &sect; <HI>XXXII.</HI> Account of the charitable corporation. &sect; <HI>XXXIII.</HI> Revival of the &s;alt-tax. &sect; <HI>XXXIV.</HI> Mr. Pulteney's name &s;truck out of the li&s;t of privy coun&s;ellors. &sect; <HI>XXXV.</HI> The king &s;ets out for Hanover.</P>
