<DIV4 N="17" TYPE="section">
<HEAD>&sect; XVII.</HEAD>
<P>The $word$ of Great-Britain meeting in November, the king $word$ $$$m to con$$$$ $word$ all $word$ expedition the proper mea&s;ures for pur&s;uing the war with vigour, that the confederate army in the Netherlands might be rea&s;onably $word$ he likewi&s;e gave them to under&s;tand, that the funds appropriated for the &s;upport of his civil government, had for &s;ome years pa&s;t fallen &s;hort of the revenue intended and granted by parliament; and $word$ he $word$ on their known affection to find out &s;ome method to make good this deficiency. As all tho&s;e who had conducted the oppo&s;ition were now concerned in the admini&s;tration, little or no objection was made to any de|mand
